name: MODERN LIVING AND FURNISHINGS
description:
Close to downtown and Uptown. Fast and convenient to highway, grocery shops, dinner, clubbing and much more. Very modern home.

Pets welcomed with approval and additional fee $100 per pet.
neighborhood_overview: Enjoy the heart of Dallas right out your door step.  Cedar Springs offers a eclectic night life as well as great restaurants.  Or take a minute drive/Uber to Uptown for shopping.
host_about:
"Love is Love" :)
I'm originally from Florida, but call Texas home.  Things I can't live without are coffee, family & friends, my dog, traveling and love. 

When I travel, I love having the comforts of home all while enjoying a new city. This was my thought when I wanted my home to a part of AirBNB. You will enjoy all the comforts of a home . . . Who doesn't like a clean, modern apartment all to themselves? All in the heart of Dallas. Come visit and stay awhile . . . You will love it!

name: 1BR 1BA Oaklawn Condo Close to Downtown & Uptown
description:
Additional discount for 2nd and 3rd month. Perfect for business or pleasure. Completely remodeled, Centrally located in Oaklawn, near downtown, medical center, trendy Uptown, shopping & restaurants. Convenient to Love airport & central to most freeways. In a quaint New Orleans Style building with Secure Parking. Smart Roku TVs,. Complete Kitchen setup. Due to HOA requirements, the minimum rental period is 30 days but you can stay for less.

Please submit purpose of visit with request.
neighborhood_overview: The address is 4340 Cedar Springs Road Dallas, TX 75219. Centrally located near many freeways including Dallas Tollway, I75, I30 and I35. Six Flags & Arlington Texas Stadium is about 30 minutes down I30.  Oak Lawn and Uptown are trendy hang out spots with lots of Restaurants, bars and shops.  Downtown is straight south on Cedar Springs Rd. There is a Kroger supermarket within walking distance, 1 1/2 block south on Cedar Springs.  There are more restaurants and shops on Lemon Ave.
host_about: I am a super host myself, I know how important it is to get a good guest.  As your guest, I will take care of your place as if it is my own.  I prefer quiet and there will be NO parties, pets, smoking, or drugs.

name: Peaceful Home By the Lake: Safe, Cozy, Quiet
description: Traveling nurses, SMU students welcome - 10% discount when you book for 3 months! Close to SMU, Fair Park, the downtown Arts/Design District, 4 blocks to the lake & 1 mile to the beautiful Arboretum. Nice neighborhood, large trees, friendly ambiance. Comfy queen bed, 3 closets, private bathroom. Watch the 72" TV (or TV in your room), enjoy high speed Wifi/work in the courtyard. Restaurants in walking distance. Bus & DART train stations close by. Runners and cyclists love it here.
neighborhood_overview: Wonderful big trees and nice sidewalks throughout the neighborhood, plus two parks within four blocks to visit.
host_about: Former high school teacher and tennis coach, I work full time now as a PR person for local neighborhood heroes and small businesses and non-profit agencies. My home is well laid out so everybody has their own space, nobody lives above or below you! Quiet neighborhood, lots of trees. A great place to live! Kind neighbors and so a great place to walk about. White Rock lake is five blocks away.

name: Uptown, Charming Studio 1B,Fast Free WiFi Parking
description:
Welcome to the Knox District, a neighborhood that needs to be appreciated. Dallas’s history rich and beloved SAFE, live-work-play destinations.

Comfortable 1 bd/1b

WALKABLE - The Katy Trail with miles of walking, jogging, and biking pleasure is a few blocks away. There are wonderful places to see and visit.

WALKABLE - Plethora of shops, restaurants, bistros, and bars (including an Apple Computer Super Store) are within easy walking distance. Trader Joe's supermarket is two blocks away.
neighborhood_overview:
Great Community to Live, Work and Play
Located in the trendy Knox Districted area of Uptown Dallas
Fabulous Central Location
Family Owned and Operated
Our Guests have said “we didn’t need our car”
THE PICTURES AND REVIEWS TELL IT ALL!!!
Lots to do with about 30 restaurants, bistros, and bars within safe, easy walking distance
Plethora of shops, boutiques and stores including a Apple Computer Super Store
Trader Joe’s Supermarket 2 blocks away
Katy Trail, Only three blocks away, it is a 15 mile long walking, jogging and biking trail

We are close to Downtown Dallas - the Arts District - Deep Ellum - Fair Park - the Science Center - Perot Science Museum – the West End District – the American Airlines Center - the Klyde Warren Park which is built over the Woodall Rodgers Freeway - George W. Bush Presidential Center and Library - Lower Greenville with all of its restaurants and nightclubs
host_about: Hello, I am Joan.  I was born in Czechoslovakia and I have lived in Czechoslovakia, Austria, Canada and now Dallas, TX.  I have traveled extensively in Europe, Canada, Costa Rica and the United States.  My favorite places are Tuscany, Italy; Prague, Czech Republic; Toronto, Canada; San Jose, Costa Rica; and southern California, plus Dallas.  I speak fluent Czech, understand most Slavic languages, and even speak a little German.  I enjoy life, exercise, the coasts and the beach, good dining, theatre, music and travel.  I love my work managing my apartments and caring for my tenants and guests.

host_about:
Come as a Stranger, Remain forever a friend~  

I grew up in New England, working in Energy I eventually found myself in Houston, Texas, over five years ago!  I am very outgoing & adventurous, love to travel, thus why I am here on AirBNB.

So in 2011 & again I 2014 I gave hosting a shot so I can meet more people traveling like myself & instantly was hooked!  Over 2 years of amazing memories of sharing time with guests from around the world and now 5 years of managing other properties. From helping with a marriage proposal, surprise birthday party with fireworks, countless meals shared along with laughter, sunrises & nightcaps with sunsets.  Now, through some fantastic friends, I have the fortune to manage a portfolio of properties in and around Houston, Dallas, San Antonio, Fairfield Bay, Arkansas & Playa Del Carmen Mexico.

It’s my commitment to provide an amazing experience while making you as comfortable as possible. Whether you are here on business or pleasure, I sincerely hope you get the most of the serenity & comfort our accommodations have to offer. If there's anything I can do to make your stay more comfortable please don't hesitate to ask!  I have two mottos, "Never A Dull Moment" (and Airbnb ceases to amaze me, in a good way) & "The Evening Has It's Plans For Us, We Simply Need To Arrive"  

To my space becoming an experience to remember!~

description: -Welcome to The Bishop Arts District situated mins from Downtown & approximately 20 minutes to Six Flags over Texas! Your Home is uniquely curated to captivate your attention, perfect for traveling families & friends, Co-Working Nomads, and Work-captioning! Bedrooms each featuring walk-in closets! neighborhood_overview:
The hip Bishop Arts District is known for its diverse nightlife, chic independent fashion stores, and colorful street art. Dining choices range from Texas-style BBQ to Vietnamese pho, while relaxed bars pour everything from cocktails to house-brewed cider. Cult movies are the draw at the Texas Theatre, while the art deco Kessler Theater presents music by local & national bands!

We welcome you to our home and proudly offer our place to use as your own. Nestled in a beautiful neighborhood where you know your neighbors, we strive to foster a great relationship with the community.

The Bishop Arts District is located in the heart of North Oak Cliff and is home to over 60 independent boutiques, restaurants, art galleries, coffee shops and bars. It is one of the most unique neighborhoods in Dallas. The hip Bishop Arts District is known for its artsy vibe, diverse nightlife, chic independent fashion stores and colorful street art. Dining choices range from Texas-style BBQ
host_about:
Come as a Stranger, Remain forever a friend~  

I grew up in New England, working in Energy I eventually found myself in Houston, Texas, over five years ago!  I am very outgoing & adventurous, love to travel, thus why I am here on AirBNB.

So in 2011 & again I 2014 I gave hosting a shot so I can meet more people traveling like myself & instantly was hooked!  Over 2 years of amazing memories of sharing time with guests from around the world and now 5 years of managing other properties. From helping with a marriage proposal, surprise birthday party with fireworks, countless meals shared along with laughter, sunrises & nightcaps with sunsets.  Now, through some fantastic friends, I have the fortune to manage a portfolio of properties in and around Houston, Dallas, San Antonio, Fairfield Bay, Arkansas & Playa Del Carmen Mexico.

It’s my commitment to provide an amazing experience while making you as comfortable as possible. Whether you are here on business or pleasure, I sincerely hope you get the most of the serenity & comfort our accommodations have to offer. If there's anything I can do to make your stay more comfortable please don't hesitate to ask!  I have two mottos, "Never A Dull Moment" (and Airbnb ceases to amaze me, in a good way) & "The Evening Has It's Plans For Us, We Simply Need To Arrive"  

To my space becoming an experience to remember!~

See all of my listings by visiting: 
https://www.airbnb.com/users/998462/listings

neighborhood_overview:
A neighborhood is known for its vibrant street murals, quirky art galleries, and long-time concert venues for indie and blues. Just east of downtown Dallas on the other side of US Route 75, Deep Ellum is the music hub of Dallas. National and local artists perform at the multitude of live music venues across town.

The most popular spots are the Bomb Factory and Trees, along with the Dallas Comedy House that offers entertaining live comedy performances. This neighborhood is a haven for lovers of music and concerts. Public bus stations are located across Deep Ellum, and the neighborhood has very easy access to major highways.

Deep Ellum has more than its fair share of local restaurants and bars. Twisted Root Burger Co., Angry Dog, Braindead Brewing, and Serious Pizza are just a significant few in the area. The music scene, the incredible variety of eateries, luxury apartments, and proximity to downtown Dallas are just a few perks of living in Deep Ellum.
